Staff
Russell Cook
Executive Director
Russell Cook joined the Silver State Health Insurance Exchange in July 2016 as the Information Systems Manager, and he has dedicated the last seven years to ensuring the success of Nevadas state-based exchange platform, NevadaHealthLink.com. He played an integral role transitioning the Exchanges operations from HealthCare.gov to NevadaHealthLink.com in 2019, and since then hes worked steadily to improve the user experience for the Exchanges consumers and enrollment partners. Russell assumed his new role as Executive Director on August 14, 2023. As a Northern Nevada native he attended Carson High School in Carson City, NV, and he received his Bachelors Degree in Music Production from the University of Southern California in Los Angeles. 
Janel Davis
Chief Operations Officer
Janel Davis served as the Communications Director at the Silver State Health Insurance Exchange for seven years. In April 2022, Janel was named the Exchanges Chief Operations Officer. In her role as Communications Director, Janel managed the marketing & advertising vendor during open enrollment and special enrollment periods and developed integrated communication strategies and outreach campaigns. Prior to the Exchange, Ms. Davis worked at the Nevada State Legislature as a Committee Secretary in the Assembly Committee on Health and Human Services and Commerce and Labor, as well as the Education and Transportation Committees. Janel graduated from the University of Nevada, Reno with a Bachelor of Arts Degree in Communications.
Jonathan Lopez
Chief Finance Officer
Jonathan Lopez joined the Silver State Health Insurance Exchange in October 2021 as the Chief Financial Officer. Previously, he worked at the Nevada Division of Public and Behavioral Health as an Administrative Services Officer (ASO) where he oversaw multiple budget accounts. Prior to being an ASO, he was the fiscal manager for the Chronic Disease Prevention and Health Promotion section where he managed various federal grants and state funds. Jonathan received his Bachelors Degree in Economics and Finance from the University of Nevada, Reno.
Shae Starbuck
Quality Assurance Manager
In December 2021, Shae Starbuck was promoted to Quality Assurance Manager. Shae joined the Silver State Health Exchange as a Program Officer in September of 2019. Shae has spent over 3 years in the Medical field. Prior to joining the Exchange Shae worked for Aguirre Health Care as an assistant denials manager. She is very excited to bring her knowledge of working with carriers to the Exchange team. Shae enjoys going to the gym and spending time her family on the Rubicon Trail.
Katie Charleson
Communications Officer
Katie Charleson joined the Silver State Health Insurance Exchange as IT Analyst in August of 2019, where she supported the communications department through marketing strategy and monitored systems within the NevadaHealthLink.com platform, especially during peak times like during Open Enrollment. In May 2022, Katie was named the Exchanges Communications Officer.
